metadata.name: GROUP THINK
metadata.description:
In the heart of bustling downtown Umeda, a crowded crosswalk pulses with unwavering urban energy. 

Faces adorned with blank stares, bodies moving without obvious purpose, the crowd embodies the raw magnetism of collective momentum. The signal changes, and the herd surges forward, a synchronized dance through asphalt arteries.

Hints of rebellion paint the scene with colorful defiance. Fashion statements challenge the status quo, but just, revealing glimpses of personal style amidst a sea of conformity.

As the crosswalk clears, the air hangs heavy with the weight of collective action. Faces remain hidden, buried in screens and obscured by masks, as the city's pulse beats on. The dance of groupthink continues, its power unyielding, as individuals merge into a single entity, destined to navigate the path of conformity together.

GROUP THINK by m0xchi

1/99
